Don't be fooled! 📸What looks like a sapphire at first glance is in fact glass paste.

📍 Sulfide mineral
📍 Found in association with chalcopyrite, quartz, rhodochrosite, and fluorite, among others
📍 Opaque black variety called marmatite
📍 Mohs scale hardness 3.5–4
